    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"small acts of caring\"... i don't even know what that means anymore. what's the point of eating or sleeping or doing anything when the person i did it all with is just... gone. it feels like i'm just a shell. i'm just going through the motions and there's nothing left inside. everything feels so pointless.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable that everything feels pointless when your world has been so fundamentally changed. When grief is that deep, basic self-care can feel monumental and overwhelming. Sometimes, the \"small acts\" are just breathing deeply, drinking a glass of water, or stepping outside for five minutes. Be gentle with yourself; you don't need to find the \"point\" right now, you just need to endure this moment.",
      "source": "target",
